product: Shower Head Lonic Filter Filtration High Pressure Water Saving 3 Mode Function Rainfall,Jetting,Massage Spray Handheld Showerheads for Dry Skin & Hair SPA (Clear)
text:
Bought one 2 years ago,  and loved it but it started dripping badly.  Since then,  have tried others but none come closer to these.  It's my preferential shower head now. Also, it has increased the water pressure(old building, old pipes, poor pressure). Fantastic product.
Read more

product: Shower Head Lonic Filter Filtration High Pressure Water Saving 3 Mode Function Rainfall,Jetting,Massage Spray Handheld Showerheads for Dry Skin & Hair SPA (Clear)
text:
was dubious about the claims made about these showerheads, but i must say so far i'm impressed, can't say if it is doing any good for my skin, but does feel good on the rainfall setting, the jet feel a lot softer than my previous showerhead, and the head holes have not clogged up due to my hard water supply and impurities therein, so must be some benefit from filtering the water
Read more

product: Shower Head Lonic Filter Filtration High Pressure Water Saving 3 Mode Function Rainfall,Jetting,Massage Spray Handheld Showerheads for Dry Skin & Hair SPA (Clear)
text:
A great shower head which results in a well-drenched shower experience!This is my third ionic shower head, although the first with a variable spray.  Water output is as expected, having used both an electric shower and pumped systems.  When it comes to cleaning, simply remove the beads and soak the head in warm, soapy water.  To re-energise the spray, remove the metal plate and soak in some limescale dissolving solution - with a little scrubbing to finish it off.It's too early to comment on longevity but it's a great head and showering experience.  The only negative was the over-sized rubber ring inside the head, which made for a poor seal and an irritating leak.  No need to return as I robbed the seal from another head which was damaged after being dropped.
Read more

product: Shower Head Lonic Filter Filtration High Pressure Water Saving 3 Mode Function Rainfall,Jetting,Massage Spray Handheld Showerheads for Dry Skin & Hair SPA (Clear)
text:
I was pleasantly surprised I really didnâ€™t think it would work but so far it is good itâ€™s increased the water pressure like it says . It was easy to install just screwed in to the hose I like the switch on the side to change the jets I think it was great value for money.
Read more

product: Shower Head Lonic Filter Filtration High Pressure Water Saving 3 Mode Function Rainfall,Jetting,Massage Spray Handheld Showerheads for Dry Skin & Hair SPA (Clear)
text:
Itâ€™s an improvement on our previous shower head, but not the magical solution to low water pressure.  Not able to use the setting where it combines the inner and outer rows.  Maybe water pressure too is low?  The water filter beads do seem to soften the water.

product: Veken 12 Inch High Pressure Rain Shower Head Combo with Extension Arm- Wide Rainfall Showerhead with 5 Handheld Water Spray - Adjustable Dual Showerhead with Anti-Clog Nozzles - Silver Chrome
text:
I have had this shower head installed for about a year now and it has held the test of time. It fits well in our standard apartment  bath/shower combo and gives it an elevated look. The pressure for handheld is super strong and I appreciate the different modes to accommodate washing your body, hair, and the shower/tub itself. It was easy to install and i didnâ€™t have any leaks with the main shower head or the hand held. It also really pause on the handheld shower head. the handle for the handheld has also stayed stuck to the wall without any movement. I would say this a pretty durable shower head with my only caveat being that the on/off cover came off and wouldnâ€™t stay on. I caught it on a deal and it was worth the price. I would buy this again

product: Veken 12 Inch High Pressure Rain Shower Head Combo with Extension Arm- Wide Rainfall Showerhead with 5 Handheld Water Spray - Adjustable Dual Showerhead with Anti-Clog Nozzles - Silver Chrome
text:
Very happy with the performance and value. Shower head looks nice, is built much better than expected (feels sturdy) and easy to install. I'm not crazy about the adhesive mount for the handheld portion, but it is a necessary compromise since I'd be less happy with drilling screws into a fiberglass shower. Be sure to clean the area with alcohol prior to sticking the mount on. Also be sure to use the included thread tape to avoid leaks (no leaks at all on ours). Handheld hose is longer than anticipated, making it great for rinsing down the shower. Selector knob allows for the use of either head or both heads at the same time. BEWARE--when changing from rain to handheld, the water left in the hose that comes out first would make a polar bear shiver if you're already happily engaged in a steamy shower. This isn't a defect or flaw, just how any shower like this would work.

product: Veken 12 Inch High Pressure Rain Shower Head Combo with Extension Arm- Wide Rainfall Showerhead with 5 Handheld Water Spray - Adjustable Dual Showerhead with Anti-Clog Nozzles - Silver Chrome
text:
Here's an HONEST review, from a Redneck, with 2 daughters, and my wife using it (and occasionally myself). We've had it installed in my daughters' bathroom for about 2 months now and so far (knock on wood) it's been great (even being used MULTIPLE times a day).(PROS)You'll knotice right off the bat when you get it, that it seems build well.. (though I wish they made the removable sprayer metal as well... but good luck finding a metal one of those in the first place). Everything assembled easily, and there's plenty of height adjustment in the "rain" shower head. I'm 5'11", and adjusted it so I wash my hair, that when my elbows go above my head, they doesn't come close to touching the sprayer head. The removable sprayer has a LONG hose, witch is GREAT. It can actually reach to the back of the tub, which is awesome to spray cleaning the back side of the tub and back tiled wall (which is AMAZING with all the hair that seems to sheds off 3 females). And a happy bonus in our case, is that it's even long enough to reach our toilet, making cleaning the toilet EASY. And the removable sprayer has a good set of spraying options.(CONS)To be honest, there's only really 1 issue I have, and 2 things I just kinda wish were different. The (1st) thing I didn't like was the removable sprayer head wall mount. It's a stick on type holder. YES it's a really strong adhesive, it was super easy to mount, and seem fine. But I guess I'm just partial to a more permanent mount style. But if you're not about drilling holes in your tile or shower wall for a permanent placement, then you'll love it. (2nd) Like I mentioned before, I SO WISH the removable sprayer head was metal. But I've tried searching for a set like this with one, and it's virtually impossible (unless you're willing to pay quite a few hundred buck). (3rd) This last one is again more of a personal preference... I wish the removable sprayer had a single stream "jet" spay (like a high pressure garden hose has). It does have a concentrated spray setting, that has plenty of pressure. But I just personally like the single spray ability (though my wife says she couldn't care less).But other than that.. It's probably exactly what you're looking for. So YES... If you're looking to get a set like this, then I'd HIGHLY RECOMMEND this one. You'll be hard pressed to find another set for this price, build quality, features, adjustability, and looks. PLUS neither my wife OUR teenage daughters have gripped at me, or complained about the shower since I put it in. I'd pay 5x as much just for that alone. I'm DEFINITELY buying another one for or master-bath (because my wife said to), and if she's happy and not gripping at me......Then I'm happy. ğŸ˜ğŸ‘

product: Bamboo Bath Mat for Inside Shower â€“ Waterproof Wood Shower Mat with Non-Slip Rubber Feet â€“ Bathroom Floor Mat for Sauna, Spa, or Outdoor Use â€“ Natural
text:
I picked up this bamboo mat for outside of mine and my husband'ss shower. I wanted to give this item a good bit of time for testing because of the fact that mold and mildew can easily be an issue on thee things after a time, and I really wanted to see with this item.  So far we have been testing this item for al most 2 full months. It has MORE than held up to the task!!!So we do have an issue with easily getting mildew, maybe mold I don't know, in our shower and certain areas in the bathroom. I'm pretty sure we are going to have to have it gutted and re-done in the not too distant future. But we aren't there yet. So, we do get that issue and have had that issue with every other mat we have tried for in front (on the outside) of our shower - until this mat. I will admit I don't wipe it down/dry it off after every single use, I think that would likely be normal for most people. Half the time it air dries and it does air dry fast. I haven't had one issue with this wooden mat. I have not has a single dot of mildew or mold grow on it anywhere. Color me truly amazed!Let me note here that we also have our Whisker Litter Robot 4 in our bathroom too, so we also deal with not only steam and water from the shower, but water from the cats playing in the sink and the toilet (both our cats love the water, weird, I know,) and then the litter that inevitably comes out when they jump out of the Litter Robot. Sometimes they jump out to the side, totally missing the litter catch mat in front of the robot, and they will jump straight on to this bamboo mat. So, I often have to get litter out from under it. But - I don't mind it because that actually keeps us from stepping on litter when we come out of the shower. So it serves a good purpose there too! I just stand it up and vacuum or sweep under it and easy peasy with regard to litter and whatever they manage to get stuck under it.This Bamboo mat has been amazing for us! You should make mental note of where it is because if you step on the edge of it you will get a little tip, but that's to be expected and its not anywhere close to a deal breaker. Its a portable off the floor wooden mat, so one should expect it to tip when it not secured to the floor. No big deal.I have zero cons for you on this. I was extra stoked because where our shower is, the space is more narrow than I would like, but it is what it is, and I was super happy to see this mat fits PERFECTLY right where I needed it to! This mat hits 5 stars from 5 in all categories on can assign to it!- Its super easy to clean or just wipe down and wipe dry.- It has NOT developed any mildew or anything nasty on it even if I don't wipe it down or dry it for a day or 3. (It air dries quite fast in my experience so there's not always a need to dry it and I'm only going to wipe it down to clean it so many times in a week)- Its the perfect size and works well when stepping out of the shower - it provides a sturdy platform and it feels sturdy to the feet and the body.- the color is nice too. I like the lighter wood color for most things regardless.Like I said, no cons. If you are in need of something like this, just get this already! This mat handles my hubby's just fine coming out of the shower. He is a big guy at 6'2" and about 215lbs. I'm smaller at 5'7" and about 115lbs, it handles us both just fine without sliding around on a wet floor. I absolutely love this mat! I absolutely suggest you get this if it is something you're looking for. It super easy to maintain and to clean, and it stays in place. Its also something that you can quite easily stand up and put out of the way if you don't want it to sit in front of your shower when its not needed. Ours stays there. So that's really up to you. This simple item has been awesome for us and we love it! I think you will too!

product: Bamboo Bath Mat for Inside Shower â€“ Waterproof Wood Shower Mat with Non-Slip Rubber Feet â€“ Bathroom Floor Mat for Sauna, Spa, or Outdoor Use â€“ Natural
text:
At first glance, this bamboo bath mat resembles something you'd find in a luxury spaâ€”simple, natural, and quietly elegant. But what surprised me more than its appearance was how functional it actually is. I placed it directly inside my walk-in shower, curious whether the "waterproof" claim would hold up. After two weeks of daily use, it has. The bamboo slats dry quickly, resist warping, and haven't developed that musty scent that typically plagues many bath mats over time.The rubber feet are small but adequate. They hold the mat securely in place, even on slippery tile, and provide just enough clearance to allow water to drain beneath without pooling. The mat feels solid when I step on itâ€”no wobbling, no squeaking, and no sense that it might tip or shift. It adds a natural, grounded feel to the otherwise sterile setting of a white-tiled shower stall.That said, this is not a plush, soft landing like a cotton rug. If you're used to cushy bathroom mats, you'll notice the difference immediately. This is structured, firm, and cool underfoot. For me, that's refreshing. It may take a moment to adjust. It's worth noting that the mat also works well outside the showerâ€”especially if you want to keep your floor dry and create a visual break between wet and dry areas.So far, maintenance has been minimal. A quick rinse and occasional towel dry keep it in good shape. The clean lines and neutral finish help it blend with almost any decor style, but it really shines in modern, Scandinavian, or spa-inspired spaces.Overall, I'm impressed. This mat strikes a balance between form and function better than I expected, offering a clean aesthetic with practical utility. Just don't expect plush comfort, it's about beauty and durability, not softness.

text:
Arrived quickly and was very well packaged. Easy to put together - laughably so if you are used to self-assembly furniture - and the fittings are of good quality. The assembled stool is very robust, certainly adequate for stability and support in a home care context, yet looks far more appealing than most that are designed for that use. It seems expensive for what it is, but is at the lower end of the price range in this context, so is good value and looks to have far better construction than anything at a lower price.The only deficiency overall was the supplied Allen key, which was a loose fit and could easily pop out in use. I used a better wrench (5mm) from my toolkit, which worked perfectly on the bolts. A very minor point but the manufacturer might consider looking at this as customers relying on the included wrench may get irritated while putting together what is actually a superb product.

product: HOLANA 18" Teak Shower Bench for Inside Shower - Wooden Shower Stool Benches Waterproof for Shaving Legs - Bench Seat with Storage Towel Shelf for Bathroom - Tub Bench Chair Spa Bath (Teak Wood)
text:
I ordered this TEAK SHOWER  STOOL for 3 reasons:1.  It was advertised to be made from TEAK wood.2.  Generous height and seat dimensions.3.  Attractive style.The stool arrived in 4 sections, along with instructions and hardware.  To my dismay, it took me over an hour to assemble a stool that should have taken no more than 5 minutes.  In fact, assembly was a downright nightmare!  Due to alignment issues with the four bolts that attach the bottom shelf to the side rails.  More specifically...â—ï¸ The bolt holes in the shelf cleats were not â€œon-centerâ€ with the blind threaded nuts in the bottom shelf.  In fact, the alignment was so bad that in some instances less than one-half of the threads were visible through the bolt hole.â—ï¸ The angle of the blind threaded nut did not always match the angle of the bolt holes.  As a result, the threads were prone to cross-threading during installation of the bolts.In the end, I was unable to install the bottom shelf without making a modification to one of the four holes.  That involved reaming the bolt hole with a 5/16â€ drill bit, then extending the one side with a rotary sanding bit.  Because this modification increased the size of the bolt hole, a larger size washer was required.In fairness, itâ€™s possible that the assembly issues that I encountered are unique to the stool that I received.  Yet thereâ€™s another problem with this shower stool that may be more universal in nature.  It appears to be made from ACACIA wood, not TEAK as advertised.  I have several pieces of TEAK furniture, and to my eye, the grain pattern and density/hardness of the wood used for the shower stool just donâ€™t agree.  But even more to the point, the box that the stool was packaged in at the factory is clearly labeled as â€œACACIA WOODâ€ (see pics).I have to admit feeling a bit duped.  Had I known this stool was ACACIA I would have never ordered it.  Not because I donâ€™t appreciate ACACIA.  Quite the contrary.  ACACIA wood is a very nice alternative to TEAK.  However, it does requires more attention to care compared to TEAK if the wood is used in a wet environment like a shower.  But the main reason I wouldnâ€™t have ordered it is because of the price.  Currently listed at $69.99, that price might be appropriate for TEAK, but not for ACACIA.As much as I would like to recommend this product, itâ€™s just too expensive for an ACACIA shower stool.  Still, it's very attractive and should work well in many applications.  But before buying, I would consider other more cost-effective options.

I love this teak table both for it's extremely aesthetically pleasing look and it's rational size. It is best described for it's waterproof capability with amazing texture and woodgrain. It is great in the bathroom but since it is strong yet small, is good for any situation. I kind of like it as a minimalist coffee table or coffee table companion but I will probably move it in to the bathroom in a couple of days since I need it in there.The table has a bottom shelf and a top shelf for cups or bottles so it would work great for storing shampoos and conditioners outside of the tub and/or shower instead of inside to free up space or so they don't get wet. But it's also really strong as a table and can hold much heavier things than just soaps and shampoos, you could pretty much sit on it, so it's very strong.  It doesn't get past my bathtub in height and if you put in a corner it could fit easily in a small bathroom.

product: Teak Corner Shower Stool â€“ 2 Tier Wooden Shower Caddy Corner Shelf Stand, Waterproof Bath Organizer for Shaving Legs, Foot Rest, Spa Decor, Bathroom Corner Storage
text:
This is a nice quality piece of Teak wood furniture.  Teak is naturally water repellent which makes it popular in shipbuilding. The pieces fit together extremely well, and it has nice touches like the "peg-in-holes" for the bottom shelf to add strength and stability.I did notice one minor dent/scuff on the wall side of both the top and bottom boards, but this will not be noticeable when placed in a corner. (See photo.)During assembly, 1 of the 3 bolts for the seat was a little tight when threading it into the receiver channel, but when I turned the whole thing upside down to make it easier to see, it made the threading easier.  I included photos to help show the basic install steps.I did try screwing in the wood screws with the included screw driver, and it was not difficult.  If you're using an electric screwdriver, be sure to set your torque setting low so you dont strip the screws.  (Probably around 4 is good.)Finished product looks great.  It could even be used for a plant stand or similar type corner table in your house.

product: Teak Shower Benches for Inside Shower â€“ Waterproof Wood Shower Stool with Storage Shelf, Non-Slip Spa Bathroom Seat Chair for Adults & Seniors, Ideal for Relaxing and Home Use
text:
Let me start by saying that I really like the quality of the wood, the finish and construction of the bench.  With that being said, there was one major issue.  It was broken upon arrival.When I received the bench, it was packaged nicely and there was not any damage to the manufacturerâ€™s box or the shipping box.  Everything was as it should be.  When I opened the manufacturerâ€™s box and unpacked all of the parts I immediately noticed the lower shelf was coming apart.  I inspected the construction and noticed the two main side slats on one side of the shelf were not glued in place.  Upon further inspection it appears the glue was applied after the wood finish was placed on the slats thus making the ability for the wood to bond together difficult.  (see attached photos).While inconvenient, this was not a deal breaker for me because I am a woodworker.  I simply sanded the involved areas and used a waterproof wood glue to bond the pieces together.  After some time clamped together everything was as intended.Upon fixing the manufacturing defect I assembled everything and then did an overall examination.  The wood is nice quality, and the finish looks good as well.  The overall construction seems decent for a self-assembled piece of furniture.  As far as overall appearance, it looks nice.My only concern is longevity.  Was the rest of the bench assembled correctly, and will it hold up over time and use?  I'm not sure.  For me, or someone with a little bit of woodworking skills, this will be easy to fix if issues arise.  For most it may be a problem.I will update my review after some time to report back on any issues if there are any.For now, while I like the way it looks, the materials used and the design, I am a little skeptical of the overall build quality.

product: Teak Shower Benches for Inside Shower â€“ Waterproof Wood Shower Stool with Storage Shelf, Non-Slip Spa Bathroom Seat Chair for Adults & Seniors, Ideal for Relaxing and Home Use
text:
I was excited to receive this beautiful teak shower bench.  It came well packaged encased in foam for protection.  All the parts were enclosed and in good shape.  When I started putting it together the legs connected to the bench easily, AND THEN the issue.  As you can see from the one picture, the one leg was missing a hole through which a bolt is supposed to connect the leg to the bench.  Without that hole, the leg would only have one point of connection and thus weaken the entire structure.  I almost just set it aside and gave up but then the review which I promised to do would not have been as valid as it could have been, so I drilled a hole where the original hole was supposed to be so I could continue.  The hole drilled extremely hard and smoked so I am not sure how the legs were made but it should not have been as hard as it was.  Anyway, it went together and fits nicely into our shower and works just fine.  The screws are exposed to water and hopefully will withstand the moisture and not rust.  Only time will tell.  They are supposed to be stainless so should be ok, but I must admit I have some reservation about quality control given the absent leg hole that I had to drill.

product: AquaDry Teak Shower Bench with Storage Shelf â€“ Premium Teak Wood Bath Seat for Spa, Bathroom, and Outdoor Use â€“ Sturdy, Compact, and Stylish Wooden Shower Stool
text:
I am actually using this table for an "off-label" purpose, it's on the deck rather than in the bathroom. But hey, if it can live in a shower it can live in rain, right? And on that front, it is doing fine, no issues getting wet causing any apparent damage. But some issues arose before that. First, during assembly on a faux hardwood floor, the varnish was easily scuffed. Now, it comes with a few little shower poofs and a bamboo soap dish, little extras but nothing huge. As for the assembly itself, six pieces to assemble, the four legs and two level surfaces. All held together by twelve screws. See where this is going? One of the holes was drilled at such a wonky angle I could not get the screw to thread in the leg. Now the top level, where the misaligned hole is, has two screws per leg, and I could either redrill the hole or just use one screw for that leg. Given having two holes sharing a terminus at one end and thirty degrees apart might end up with the screw offering minimal support, and that I intend to use it exclusively as a table and not a stool, I went with just one screw. Is it still stable? Yes. Will it's max weight be lower? Presumably but I don't intend to find out. So, simple furniture with water resistance/tolerance, good, quality control however, lackluster.

text:
It wasn't difficult to put together except for the fact that one of the screws didn't want to go in all of the way so there's a small gap in one corner. You have to do A LOT of screwing in with the Alan wrench so that's tiring. The table/bench itself is really nicely made and very sturdy once built. It also comes with a little soap tray and 3 loofahs. I actually ended up using it outside as a plant stand near our pool because it was too large for our shower. It's lightweight but holds up really well through the continuous water being on it.
